## Channel Plugin Architecture Patterns - IRC and Nostr Extensions

Based on my thorough exploration of the IRC and Nostr channel plugins, here is the complete pattern for creating a new channel plugin:

---

### **FILE STRUCTURE & ORGANIZATION**

Each channel plugin (`extensions/<id>/`) contains:

```
extensions/<id>/
├── package.json                    # NPM package metadata
├── openclaw.plugin.json            # Plugin manifest
├── index.ts                        # Main plugin entry point
├── setup-entry.ts                  # Setup wizard entry
├── api.ts                          # Public API barrel
├── channel-config-api.ts           # (IRC only) Channel config exports
├── runtime-api.ts                  # (Nostr) Re-exports from src/
├── src/
│   ├── types.ts                    # Core type definitions & account resolution
│   ├── runtime.ts                  # Runtime store setup
│   ├── channel.ts                  # Main plugin implementation (createChatChannelPlugin)
│   ├── config-schema.ts            # JSON schema for config validation
