### **SUMMARY OF KEY FILES & THEIR ROLES**

| File | Purpose | Key Exports |
|------|---------|------------|
| `package.json` | NPM metadata + OpenClaw manifest | `openclaw` block defines channel in UI |
| `openclaw.plugin.json` | Plugin discovery manifest | `id`, `channels`, `configSchema` |
| `index.ts` | Main entry point | `defineChannelPluginEntry()` |
| `setup-entry.ts` | Setup wizard entry | `defineSetupPluginEntry()` |
| `api.ts` | Public API barrel | Re-exports from `src/` |
| `src/types.ts` | Type defs + account resolution | `*AccountConfig`, `Resolved*Account`, resolvers |
| `src/runtime.ts` | Runtime store setup | `get/setRuntime` |
| `src/channel.ts` | Main plugin (via `createChatChannelPlugin`) | `channelPlugin` instance |
| `src/config-schema.ts` | JSON schema for validation | Config schema for TypeScript config |
| `src/setup-*.ts` | Setup UI/wizard | Setup adapters |
| Other `src/` files | Implementation details | Channel-specific (client, monitor, send, etc.) |

This comprehensive pattern allows OpenClaw to discover, initialize, and manage channel plugins with consistent interfaces while allowing channel-specific customization through type generics and helper functions.

